President Barack Obama has established the White House Council for Community Solutions to provide advice on mobilizing citizens, nonprofits, businesses, and government to work together to solve community needs. He has appointed various individuals to the council, including Patty Stonesifer as Chair, Byron Auguste, Diana Aviv, Paula Boggs, Jon Bon Jovi, and others. The council will focus on enlisting leaders in the nonprofit, private, and philanthropic sectors to achieve policy goals, promoting innovation and collaboration, and honoring those making a significant impact in their communities.